.TH NOOPT 3RPG  "June 2012" "ILE RPG Language Reference"
.SH NAME
NOOPT
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fINOOPT\fR keyword indicates that no optimization is to be performed on the standalone field, parameter or data structure for which this keyword is specified\[char46] Specifying \fINOOPT\fR ensures that the content of the data item is the latest assigned value\[char46] This may be necessary for those fields whose values are used in exception handling\[char46] 





If a data item which is to be passed by reference is defined with the \fINOOPT\fR keyword, then any prototype or procedure interface parameter definition must also have the \fINOOPT\fR keyword specified\[char46] This requirement does not apply to parameters passed by value\[char46]


All keywords allowed for standalone field definitions, parameters, or data structure definitions are allowed with \fINOOPT\fR\[char46]

.SH NOTICE
Tip: 
Any data item defined in an \fIOPM\fR \fIRPG\fR/400Â® program is implicitly defined with \fINOOPT\fR\[char46] So if you are creating a prototype for an \fIOPM\fR program, you should specify \fINOOPT\fR for all parameters defined within the prototype\[char46] This will avoid errors for any users of the prototype\[char46]


